Purpose
The purpose of this task is to identify and prioritize the core functionalities of the MVP from the user’s perspective and to visualize its interface where applicable.

User Stories (MoSCoW Prioritization)
Must Have

As a hackathon participant, I want to create a profile with my skills and preferred role, so that teams can easily find suitable members.
As a team leader, I want to create a team and define required roles, so that I can fill missing positions quickly.
As a user, I want to browse available teams and participants, so that I can choose the best match.
As a team member, I want to view team composition, so that I know which roles are filled.

Should Have

As a user, I want to send join requests to teams, so that team formation is organized.
As a team leader, I want to accept or reject join requests, so that my team remains balanced.
As a user, I want to update my availability status, so that others know if I am open to joining.

Could Have

As a user, I want to receive suggested teams or members based on skills, so that team formation becomes faster.
As a user, I want to chat with teammates, so that communication is easier.
As a user, I want to receive notifications for new requests or matches, so that I stay informed.


 Won’t Have (Out of Scope for MVP)

As a user, I want advanced AI personality matching, so that teams are perfectly optimized.
As a user, I want detailed post-hackathon ratings and analytics.


Mockups
The MVP includes a user interface.
Mockups were created using Figma to visualize the main screens, including:

User profile creation
Team creation and discovery
Team management
MVP feature prioritization

The mockups focus on layout and user flow rather than final visual design.
